extends layout

block content
  #banner.container
    .rays   
    .text
      .intro Web framework for Node.js using <strong>generators</strong>
      .get-started
        a.btn.btn-primary(href="/guide.html") Guide
        a.btn.btn-primary(href="/examples/index.html") Examples
        a.btn.btn-primary(href="/api/index.html") API
      .version v#{version}
      .meta
        iframe(src="http://ghbtns.com/github-btn.html?user=waigo&repo=waigo&type=watch&size=small&count=true", allowtransparency="true", frameborder="0", scrolling="0", width="62", height="20")
        iframe(src="http://ghbtns.com/github-btn.html?user=waigo&repo=waigo&type=fork&size=small&count=true", allowtransparency="true", frameborder="0", scrolling="0", width="62", height="20")

  section#details1
    h2 What is Waigo?
    :markdown
      Waigo is a Node.js framework for building scalable web applications. Waigo uses [ES6 generators](http://wingolog.org/archives/2013/05/08/generators-in-v8) and an innovative architecture 
      to improve upon the current generation of frameworks.
    .features.row
      .col-md-4
        h3 Easy
        ul
          li Built on <a href="http://koajs.com" target="_blank">Koa/Express</a> middleware architecture.
          li <a href="/guide.html#command-line">Command-line</a> client to automate tasks.
      .col-md-4
        h3 Elegant
        ul
          li No more callback hell. Generators and promises are in.
          li <a href="/api">Minimal core</a> framework, with no unneeded cruft.
      .col-md-4
        h3 Extendable
        ul
          li Easily <a href="/guide.html#extend-and-override">override</a> framework behaviour.
          li Create and share customizations as <a href="/guide.html#plugins">plugins</a>.

  section#details2
    h2 Quick start
    .row
      .col-md-6
        pre
          code.language-bash
            $ npm install -g waigo
            $ waigo init
            $ ./start-app.js
      .col-md-6
        :markdown 
          If you visit `http://localhost:3000` in your browser you should see 
          some welcome text.

          You can now start adding controllers and models and develop your 
          application.


